Former Vice President, Atiku Abubakar, is set to hold a world-press conference today in Abuja. Atiku who lost the recently conducted presidential polls to President Muhammadu Buhari of the All Progressive’s Congress, (APC), is expected to speak on the elections. The event is expected to hold by 4:pm at Musa Yar’adua centre says Col Austin Akobundu (rtd), National Organizing Secretary of the PDP presidential campaign organisation. Atiku contested as the candidate of the people’s Democratic Party, (PDP) Atiku to hold world press briefing in Abuja today BREAKING: PDP set for protest at US embassy over Buhari's handling of Nigeria Kannywood star Zango endorses Atiku